I had my first time at this place tonight. I ordered chicken quesadilla with corn tortillas for dinner. Before making it the chef double checked my order by asking me...so he wanted to make sure he makes my food the way I wanted. They seem very friendly, extremely clean and the ambiance, style is minimal with Mexican tiles. It's interesting. Most importantly, the food was very good! They use good quality tortillas, you can taste the corn aromas. The quesadilla was served with lime slice, reddish and cucumber slices. There is not a lot of good restaurants in my neighborhood, but this one has become my go to. I can't wait to come back again!
